news.title: Centre approves housing scheme for slum dwellers in Kolhapur
news.para: An official from Kolhapur Municipal Corporation (KMC) claimed that the housing project for the slum dwellers is the first to be sanctioned in the state.

news.title: Vadodara civic body set to kick off Sahakarnagar housing project
news.para: The civic body had razed 1,428 dwellings and 78 shops at the site promising them houses in a scheme for the urban poor at the same site, but the project is yet to take off.

news.title: Kolkata civic body relief on property tax arrears
news.para: Sources in KMC said following a hue and cry over bills that increased the tax by 20%-30% following calculation of pending GRs, the civic body has decided to reduce the rate of hike from 10% per GR each cycle if the pendancy is over six years.

news.title: Karnataka government directs BBMP to issue A Khata to B Khata properties
news.para: The decision was taken at a meeting headed by Chief Secretary P Ravikumar, after which a letter was sent by the Department of Urban Development to BBMP Chief Commissioner.

news.title: Gurugram civic body panels set up for survey to regularise illegal colonies
news.para: If the colonies meet the criteria set by the government, they will be covered under the regularisation policy. Each team comprises junior engineers and patwaris, who will cover 60 unauthorised colonies.

news.title: Mumbai: Over 300 shaky buildings need to be vacated before rains
news.para: According to BMC rules, residents living in all buildings that are over 30 years old have to carry out a structural audit of the buildings. Those buildings that are found to be in the C1 category and can’t be repaired have to be vacated.

news.title: Gurugram: DTCP tells realtors to check violations in licensed colonies
news.para: At a meeting with some 100 realtors from Gurgaon Home Developers and Plot Holders Association on Tuesday, district town planner (enforcement) RS Batth also made it clear that tree felling for construction purposes without the permission of the authorities concerned shall be considered as an offence.

news.title: MahaRERA permits buyer to exit project due to false information in brochure
news.para: The order issued by MahaRERA member Vijay Satbir Singh on April 22 for a project in the state allowed the homebuyer to withdraw from that with a refund and interest over false representation in brochures by the developer under Section 12 of the Real Estate Regulatory Act (RERA) 2016.

news.title: Just 4% real estate related cases under insolvency & bankruptcy resolved
news.para: This represents just 4% of cases accepted, compared to overall resolution rate of 9% under IBC, it said. The poor resolution rate further delays reprieve for thousands of homebuyers left in the lurch by builders.

news.title: Bajaj Finance infuses Rs 2,500 crore into Bajaj Housing Finance
news.para: The capital, which was received on April 7, is the seventh and the largest round of capital infusion so far by Bajaj Finance to fund the housing finance company's future growth, according to a release.

news.title: Macrotech Developers posts net profit of Rs 1,202 crore in FY22
news.para: Total income rose to Rs 9,579.17 crore in the 2021-22 financial year from Rs 5,771.65 crore in the previous fiscal. Net profit rose to Rs 535.46 crore in the fourth quarter of last fiscal from Rs 310.56 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: IWG revenue jumps nearly 18% to $782 million in Jan-March
news.para: Workspace landlords like IWG are recovering gradually from the pandemic as people return to offices and businesses choose hybrid work models where employees split time between home and office.

news.title: China property firms joined central bank talks on ways to help sector: Sources
news.para: The central bank said last week it had held discussions with banks and asset management firms to discuss support for the economy and property sector, but it had not indicated that property developers had also been invited.

news.title: Omaxe raises Rs 440 crore from Varde Partners to expedite construction, expand business
news.para: The company will deploy the funds for expediting construction and delivery of its projects as well as for expansion, according to a regulatory filing.

news.title: Probe illegal sand activity in Goa: HC to chief secretary, DGP
news.para: The court also directed the in-charge of Pernem police station and mamlatdar to file a detailed affidavit about the incidents.
